text: Today sucks.
I had 2 call offs last night at work whi h would have left only me to supervise a house of 6 people, but we managed to get someone to come in.
Then our one overnighter called off 2 hours before his shift, our second overnighter was willing to do it alone, but needed to leave at 6 sharp. We only have one scheduled to come in at 6.
Another staff was in at 7, but we still needed someone there for an hour.
So, I said I'd do it.
This morning, I'm up and out the door on time, despite being there until 11 last night, and I hit a fucking hellspwan of a pothole, landing me with a flat tire.
Our overnighter ended up having to take one of the ladies with her at 6 to maintain supervision. Now I have to go get a new tire with 2 kids. :face_with_rolling_eyes:
Yikes.
Sorry man.
Day in the life.
Jesus, sorry about hearing all that, Dean O.o That's rough.
Thanks. Just needed to vent a little.
I'm sitting on the couch watching cartoons with my kids, eating toast. When they're done we'll go to the tire place.

Speaking of Pokemon
My two older boys have been playing Let's Go Pikachu on the Switch together
Super excited when I helped them get the Bulbasaur and Charmander.
Let’s Go was such a breath of fresh air. It was such a good game for so many reasons
It does present a bit of an issue for new players in that no other game, minus Pokemon Go on mobile devices, has the same leveling engine
My kids did not get why they had to catch the same Pokemon over and over again
I can definitely see that, but aside from minor gameplay oddities, it was a great way to get a younger audience in, or bridge the gap between PoGo and the main series games
Having said that, I do actually hope SwSh keeps it. Was honestly faster and easier than the grind of mind-numbingly KO'ing Caterpies
